.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:8:<!-- Keywords: system-deep-loop, deep-loop, deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, deep-improvement, deep-alignment, alignment, conformance, standard-authority, alignment-lane, conformance-review, read-only-default, context-gathering, reuse-catalog, autoresearch, iterative-research, review-loop, deep-review-wave, release-readiness, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, ai-council, council-deliberation, multi-seat-planning, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, model-benchmark, skill-benchmark, convergence-detection, externalized-state, coverage-graph, mode-registry, workflowmode, runtimeloop-type, backendkind -->
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:9:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:10:# System Deep Loop
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:11:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:12:One skill, five active workflow families, one nested runtime layer. `system-deep-loop` is the public, advisor-routable home for active deep-loop personas; `runtime/` is the frozen, MCP-free infrastructure layer it consumes (formerly the separate `deep-loop-runtime` skill, merged into this hub 2026-07-08). This hub holds NO per-mode convergence, state, or synthesis logic — each active mode keeps its own contract in its packet, and the hub only routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:13:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:14:Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, `/deep:research` for iterative investigation with a bounded context snapshot, `/deep:review` for iterative audit with a bounded review snapshot, `/deep:alignment` for read-only-by-default conformance against a named standard authority, or `/speckit:plan` for implementation planning.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:15:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:16:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:17:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:18:## 1. WHEN TO USE
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:19:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:20:Use this skill (through the hub) for any active deep-loop workflow. Invoke it as `Skill(system-deep-loop)` (optionally with a mode hint such as `research: <request>` or `alignment: <request>`); the hub classifies the request, resolves a `workflowMode`, and loads the matching nested mode packet. Active `/deep:*` commands and native agent types remain as complementary surfaces over the same packets.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:21:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:22:| Mode | Use it for | Packet | Command | Agent |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:23:|------|-----------|--------|---------|-------|
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:24:| **research** | Outward, web + code iterative investigation → `research/research.md` | `system-deep-loop/deep-research/` | `/deep:research` | `deep-research` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:25:| **review** | Iterative review loop → P0/P1/P2 findings + verdict | `system-deep-loop/deep-review/` | `/deep:review` | `deep-review` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:26:| **ai-council** | Multi-seat planning deliberation → `ai-council/**` artifacts | `system-deep-loop/deep-ai-council/` | `/deep:ai-council` | `ai-council` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:27:| **improvement** (3 lanes) | Evaluator-first improvement: `agent-improvement`, `model-benchmark`, `skill-benchmark` | `system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/` | `/deep:agent-improvement` · `/deep:model-benchmark` · `/deep:skill-benchmark` | `deep-improvement` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:28:| **alignment** | Read-only-by-default conformance audit against a named standard authority | `system-deep-loop/deep-alignment/` | `/deep:alignment` | `deep-alignment` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:29:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:30:### When NOT to Use
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:31:- A single quick read/edit (no loop) — use the relevant code or doc skill directly.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:32:- Backend/runtime support (executor, coverage-graph, scoring, fan-out) — that is `runtime/`, consumed here, not invoked as a user workflow (formerly the separate deep-loop-runtime skill).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:33:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:34:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:35:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:36:## 2. SMART ROUTING
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:37:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:38:Routing is **registry-driven** (invokable-hub, Option E). `mode-registry.json` is the single source of truth; the hub reads it and does not re-derive the mapping. When invoked as `Skill(system-deep-loop[, "<mode>: <request>"])`, the hub classifies the request to a `workflowMode`, resolves it through the registry, and loads `registry[mode].packet`. The advisor routes any deep-loop query to the single identity `system-deep-loop`; the hub then picks the mode. The `/deep:*` commands and native agent types remain as complementary surfaces — they reach the same packets through static routers/agent definitions — and the hub holds NO per-mode logic.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:39:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:40:> **Compiled routing (opt-in, flag-gated, additive).** When `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, resolve the mode via the compiled router contract first:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:41:> ```bash
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:42:> node .opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs --hub system-deep-loop --prompt "<task>"
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:43:> ```
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:44:> Follow the returned decision — `route` (use its `targets`), `clarify`/`defer` (disambiguate), `reject` (refuse). On a `{"servingAuthority":"legacy"}` sentinel or any error, use the routing below. The front door self-gates on serving-authority, and the flag is **off by default**, so this is inert until compiled routing is activated for `system-deep-loop`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:45:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:46:This hub is an intent/registry router, not a keyed resource-discovery router: at runtime it omits `discover_markdown_resources` and only guards registry-selected packet loads, never selecting hub-level `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` resources by runtime key. It does carry a second-layer surface router at `shared/references/smart-routing.md` — a benchmark/replay artifact (mirroring sk-prompt/sk-code) that maps a resolved mode's intent to packet-qualified child leaves so router-replay can emit canonical `{workflowMode, leafResourceId}` typed pairs against `leaf-manifest.json`. That surface layer never re-decides the mode and is not a runtime hub discovery surface; the hub still routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json` alone.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:47:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:48:### Note on the frontmatter `allowed-tools` grant
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:49:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:50:The hub's own routing logic is read-only (classify, guard a path, load a packet). The frontmatter `allowed-tools` list is nonetheless broad because, per the two-axis hub canon contract, a hub's tool grant MUST equal the exact union of every registered mode's `toolSurface.allowed` in `mode-registry.json` — not the tool set the hub's own logic uses. This is a hard invariant enforced by `parent-skill-check.cjs` (check 3j: "hub allowed-tools equals the union of mode tool surfaces"); narrowing the frontmatter grant to only what routing-only logic needs would fail that check and break every mode whose `toolSurface` isn't a subset of the narrowed list. Treat the breadth of `allowed-tools` as evidence of the child modes' combined needs, not of mutating logic living in the hub.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:51:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:52:### The three-tier discriminator
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:53:- **`workflowMode`** — the public active mode key: `research`, `review`, `ai-council`, `alignment`, and the three improvement lanes `agent-improvement`, `model-benchmark`, `skill-benchmark`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:54:- **`runtimeLoopType`** — the graph-backed convergence key consumed by `runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` (validated against active `research|review|council`). **Explicit `null` for all three improvement lanes; never inferred from `workflowMode`.** Note `ai-council` maps to `runtimeLoopType: council`, while `alignment` maps to `runtimeLoopType: review`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:55:- **`backendKind`** — which backend runs the mode: `runtime-loop-type` (research/review/ai-council/alignment) or `improvement-host` (`deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs --mode`).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:56:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:57:### Routing rule
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:58:```
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:59:classify the request to a workflowMode (dominant deep-loop intent; mode hint like "research: ..." overrides)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:60:guard mode-registry.json inside SKILL_ROOT and read it as data
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:61:if classifier confidence is low or no mode dominates:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:62:  → return UNKNOWN_FALLBACK with a disambiguation checklist: choose research, review, ai-council, alignment, or one improvement lane
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:63:else:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:64:  → resolve workflowMode from the hint / classified intent (or the /deep:* command / advisor alias)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:65:  → find registry[mode]; if missing, return UNKNOWN_FALLBACK instead of loading a guessed path
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:66:  → guard registry[mode].packet/SKILL.md inside SKILL_ROOT and load it only if the packet directory and SKILL.md both exist
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:67:       e.g. registry["research"].packet → system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:68:       e.g. registry["alignment"].packet → system-deep-loop/deep-alignment/SKILL.md
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:69:       (the 3 improvement modes all share the system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/ packet)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:70:  → if registry[mode].runtimeLoopType !== null: backend = convergence.cjs --loop-type <runtimeLoopType>
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:71:     else: backend = improvement loop-host (--mode), per backendKind
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:72:```
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:73:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:74:Router-driven loads MUST use `_guard_in_skill(relative_path)` before `load()`, reject paths that escape this skill or do not end in `.md`, and check `if packet_base.exists()` plus `if packet_skill.exists()` before loading. The fallback must name the unresolved `workflowMode` when known, avoid loading any guessed packet, and ask the operator to provide one of the registered modes or the matching `/deep:*` command.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:75:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:76:Intent classification favors the single dominant active deep-loop mode; a mode hint (`research: ...`, `review: ...`, `ai-council: ...`, `alignment: ...`, or an improvement lane) overrides the classifier. The legacy advisor projection maps stay hardcoded and drift-guarded against the registry, and the command files remain static routers with hardcoded asset/mode routing; neither resolves from `mode-registry.json` at runtime, but both stay equal to its projection.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:77:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:78:Per-mode behavior is **not flattened**: each active packet keeps its own convergence math, state shape, artifacts, and tool-permission guards (research has WebFetch; review/ai-council are code/inward-only; alignment is a named-standard, read-only-by-default conformance audit; improvement is the only direct mutation family). Exactly one `graph-metadata.json` — this hub's — is preserved, so the advisor discovers exactly one skill identity regardless of which surface (hub `Skill()`, `/deep:*` command, or agent) reaches a mode.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:79:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:80:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:81:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:82:## 3. HOW IT WORKS
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:83:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:84:### Layout
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:85:```
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:86:system-deep-loop/
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:87:  SKILL.md               # this routing hub (no per-mode logic)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:88:  mode-registry.json     # the three-tier discriminator + advisorRouting (single source of truth)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:89:  graph-metadata.json    # the ONE advisor identity for the whole skill
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:90:  deep-research/   deep-review/   deep-ai-council/   deep-improvement/   deep-alignment/   # active mode packets
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:91:  shared/synthesis/      # workflows-shared synthesis (e.g. emitResourceMap)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:92:```
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:93:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:94:Each active mode packet keeps its own `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `scripts/`, `assets/`, `feature-catalog/`, or `manual-testing-playbook/` as applicable, with internal paths repointed and **no per-packet `graph-metadata.json`** — only this hub carries one, so the advisor discovers exactly one skill. The `deep-ai-council` packet folder follows the standard `folder == packetSkillName` convention (`deep-ai-council`); its legacy public surfaces (the `/deep:ai-council` command and the `ai-council` agent) intentionally keep the shorter `ai-council` key, so always resolve the packet path through `mode-registry.json` rather than hardcoding it.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:95:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:96:### Backend
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:97:All modes consume `runtime/` (frozen, MCP-free): executor config, prompt-pack, validation, atomic state, coverage-graph, Bayesian scoring, fan-out, the council primitives, and the promoted plumbing (capability resolver, artifact-root, loop-lock CLI, lifecycle taxonomy). The runtime never gains an `improvement` loopType — improvement stays host-driven.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:98:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:99:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:100:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:101:## 4. RULES
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:102:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:103:### ✅ ALWAYS
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:104:- **ALWAYS** resolve a mode through `mode-registry.json` (read the `packet` key; never hardcode a router mapping or packet path in the hub).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:105:- **ALWAYS** keep advisor projection maps hardcoded and drift-guarded against the registry; command mode routing is still hardcoded in the command files and does not resolve through `mode-registry.json`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:106:- **ALWAYS** keep each mode's convergence/state/artifact contract in its packet — the hub stays logic-free.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:107:- **ALWAYS** keep exactly one `graph-metadata.json` (this hub's) so the advisor sees one skill identity, whether a mode is reached via `Skill(system-deep-loop)`, a `/deep:*` command, or an agent.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:108:- **ALWAYS** keep `Skill(system-deep-loop)` hub routing, the `/deep:*` commands, and the agent types as complementary surfaces over the same packets — never let one surface fork per-mode logic out of its packet.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:109:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:110:### ⛔ NEVER
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:111:- **NEVER** add an `improvement` `loopType` to `runtime/convergence.cjs` (improvement is host-driven; `runtimeLoopType` stays `null`).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:112:- **NEVER** infer `runtimeLoopType` from `workflowMode` — read it from the registry (explicit `null` is load-bearing).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:113:- **NEVER** let a read-only mode (research/review/ai-council/alignment) reach the improvement mutation scripts (`promote-candidate.cjs`/`rollback-candidate.cjs`).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:114:- **NEVER** add a `graph-metadata.json` or a discoverable skill marker inside a mode packet or `shared/`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:115:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:116:### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:117:- A new mode is needed beyond the seven registered — extend `mode-registry.json` and open a packet, do not bolt logic onto the hub.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:118:- A change would require the runtime to gain MCP tools or an improvement loopType — that contradicts the architecture; escalate.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:119:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:120:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:121:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:122:## 5. REFERENCES
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:123:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:124:- Backend: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/` (frozen, consumed by every mode; nested infrastructure, not a separate skill).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:125:- Mode packets: `deep-research/SKILL.md`, `deep-review/SKILL.md`, `deep-ai-council/SKILL.md`, `deep-improvement/SKILL.md`, `deep-alignment/SKILL.md` (per-mode detail).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:126:- Commands: the active `/deep:*` commands under `.opencode/commands/deep/` (complementary surface).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:127:- Registry: `mode-registry.json` (the routing contract — the authoritative `packet` paths).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:128:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:129:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:130:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:131:## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:132:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:133:- The hub resolves one primary active `workflowMode` for the request through `mode-registry.json` (improvement folds to the right lane via the registry, never by array order).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:134:- The selected mode packet owns the detailed convergence/state/artifact workflow; the hub stayed routing-only.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:135:- `Skill(system-deep-loop[, hint])` reaches a mode, and the `/deep:*` commands and agent types still reach the same packets.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:136:- Exactly one `graph-metadata.json` exists for the whole skill; no packet carries its own.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:137:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:138:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:139:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:140:## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:141:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:142:### Modes
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:143:- `research` — outward web + code iterative investigation (`research/research.md`).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:144:- `review` — iterative review loop, P0/P1/P2 findings + verdict.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:145:- `ai-council` — multi-seat planning deliberation (`ai-council/**` artifacts).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:146:- `improvement` (3 lanes) — evaluator-first agent/model/skill improvement.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:147:- `alignment` — read-only-by-default conformance audit against a named standard authority (`alignment/` artifacts).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:148:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:149:### Surfaces and Consumers
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:150:- `Skill(system-deep-loop)` is the invokable hub; active `/deep:*` commands and the agent types (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `ai-council`, `deep-improvement`, `deep-alignment`) are complementary surfaces over the same packets.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:151:- `runtime/` is the frozen, MCP-free backend every mode consumes (nested infrastructure, not a separate skill).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:152:- `/speckit:plan` consumes `@context` packages plus research/review/alignment outputs; spec-folder docs consume research/review/alignment output.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:153:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:154:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:155:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:156:## 8. RELATED RESOURCES
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:157:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:158:- Pattern: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/references/parent-skill/parent-skills-nested-packets.md` (parent-skill hub + nested packets, the one-graph-metadata invariant).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:159:- Sibling example: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/` (the same invokable-hub + `mode-registry.json` Option E pattern).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:160:- Registry: `mode-registry.json` (this hub's routing contract).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:1:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:2:name: deep-research
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:3:description: "Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation, externalized state, convergence detection, fresh context per pass."
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:4:allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, memory_context, memory_search]
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:5:argument-hint: "[topic] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]"
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:6:version: 1.14.0.0
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:7:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:8:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:9:<!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:10:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:11:# Autonomous Deep Research Loop
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:12:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:13:Note: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:14:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:15:Iterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:16:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:17:Runtime path resolution: OpenCode/Copilot runtime uses `.opencode/agents/*.md`; Claude runtime uses `.claude/agents/*.md`.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:18:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:19:Operator contract precedence for this skill surface (highest first): command entrypoint syntax in `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`; convergence math in `references/convergence/convergence.md` and the deep-research YAML workflow; runtime agent inventories from the checked-in runtime directories above.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:20:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:21:### Convergence Threshold Semantics
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:22:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:23:**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:24:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:25:**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:26:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:27:**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:28:- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:29:- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:30:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:31:Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts; see this skill's changelog/decision records for the parity research confirming thresholds do not carry across siblings.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:32:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:33:## 1. WHEN TO USE
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:34:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:35:### Activation Triggers
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:36:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:37:Use this skill when:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:38:- Deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:39:- Topic spans 3+ technical domains or sources
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:40:- Initial findings need progressive refinement
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:41:- Overnight or unattended research sessions
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:42:- Research where prior findings inform subsequent queries
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:43:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:44:Keyword triggers:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:45:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:46:- `autoresearch`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:47:- `deep research`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:48:- `autonomous research`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:49:- `research loop`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:50:- `iterative research`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:51:- `multi-round research`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:52:- `deep investigation`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:53:- `comprehensive research`
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:54:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:55:### Use Cases
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:56:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:57:Use deep-research for multi-round technical investigation, source triangulation, repeated exploration with fresh context, and research sessions where prior findings should shape the next focus.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:58:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:59:### When NOT to Use
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:60:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:61:- Simple, single-question research (use direct codebase search or `/speckit:plan`)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:62:- Known-solution documentation (use `/speckit:plan`)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:63:- Implementation tasks (use `/speckit:implement`)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:64:- Quick codebase searches (use `@context` or direct Grep/Glob)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:65:- Fewer than 3 sources needed (single-pass research suffices)
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:66:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:67:---
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:68:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:69:## 2. SMART ROUTING
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:70:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:71:> Pattern: aligned with the [sk-doc smart-router resilience template](../../sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill-smart-router.md).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:72:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:73:### Resource Domains
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:74:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:75:The router discovers markdown resources from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies intent scoring from `RESOURCE_MAP`. Keep routing domain-focused rather than hardcoding exhaustive inventories.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:76:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:77:- `references/guides/quick-reference.md` -- first-touch operator cheat sheet.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:78:- `references/protocol/loop-protocol.md` -- lifecycle, dispatch, reducer sequencing, command-owned state flow.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:79:- `references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md` -- bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:80:- `references/convergence*.md` -- stop contracts, signals, recovery, graph gates, reference-only convergence ideas.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:81:- `references/state*.md` -- packet layout, JSONL records, markdown outputs, reducer ownership, reconstruction.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:82:- `references/guides/capability-matrix.md` -- runtime parity.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:83:- `assets/*.md` -- markdown templates and prompt assets safe for guarded markdown loading.
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:84:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:85:### Resource Loading Levels
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:86:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:87:| Level | When to Load | Resources |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:88:|-------|--------------|-----------|
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:89:| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | Quick reference baseline |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:90:| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop, convergence, state, spec anchoring, runtime parity references |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:91:| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full reference set and markdown assets |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:92:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:93:### Phase Signals
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:94:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:95:| Phase | Signal | Primary Resources |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:96:|-------|--------|-------------------|
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:97:| Init | No JSONL exists or setup context | `loop-protocol.md`, `state-format.md`, `state-jsonl.md` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:98:| Iteration | Dispatch context includes iteration number | `loop-protocol.md`, `state-outputs.md`, `convergence-signals.md` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:99:| Stuck | Dispatch context includes recovery language | `convergence-recovery.md`, `state-reducer-registry.md` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:100:| Synthesis | STOP candidate or final report | `convergence.md`, `state-outputs.md`, `spec-check-protocol.md` |
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:101:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:102:### Smart Router Pseudocode
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:103:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:104:The authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, ambiguity handling, and graceful fallback, via four patterns: runtime discovery (`discover_markdown_resources()` scans `references/`/`assets/`), existence-check-before-load (`load_if_available()` guards paths against `inventory` and `seen`), extensible routing keys (intent labels map to resource families, not static file lists), and multi-tier graceful fallback (`UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` for disambiguation; missing families return a helpful notice).
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:105:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:106:```python
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:107:from pathlib import Path
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:108:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:109:SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:110:RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / "references", SKILL_ROOT / "assets")
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:111:DEFAULT_RESOURCE = "references/guides/quick-reference.md"
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:112:
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:113:INTENT_SIGNALS = {
.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md:114:    "LOOP_SETUP": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["autoresearch", "deep research", "research loop", "autonomous research", "setup", "init"]},
