.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:12:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:13:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:14:# Alignment Verification Automation
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:15:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:16:This document describes the repeatable verifier introduced for recurring alignment drift checks.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:17:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:18:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:19:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:20:### Purpose
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:21:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:22:Defines the operational contract for `verify_alignment_drift.py`, including:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:23:- what rule categories are enforced;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:24:- how severities (`ERROR`/`WARN`) are assigned;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:25:- default vs strict CI failure behavior.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:26:- which standards remain manual checklist gates.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:27:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:28:### When to Use
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:29:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:30:Use this reference when tuning recurring checks or interpreting verifier output in automation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:31:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:32:## 2. SCRIPT
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:33:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:34:- Path: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py`
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:35:- Purpose: run lightweight, deterministic, behavior-neutral checks across OpenCode system languages.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:36:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:37:## 3. WHAT IT CHECKS
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:38:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:39:- **Common (all scanned files)**: UTF-8 readability and LF line endings (flags CRLF).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:40:- **JavaScript (`.js/.cjs`)**: requires `'use strict';` near file top.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:41:- **JavaScript ESM (`.mjs`)**: strict-mode directive is not enforced.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:42:- **TypeScript (`.ts/.tsx/.mts`)**: requires a `MODULE:` header marker near file top, except test files and pattern assets.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:43:- **Python (`.py`)**: requires `#!/usr/bin/env python3` and module docstring near file top.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:44:- **Shell (`.sh`)**: requires `#!/usr/bin/env bash` and `set -euo pipefail` near file top.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:45:- **JSON (`.json`)**: strict parser validation via Python `json` module, with comment-aware fallback for `tsconfig*.json`.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:46:- **JSONC (`.jsonc`)**: comment stripping followed by strict JSON parse.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:47:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:48:### What it does not check
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:49:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:50:The verifier is intentionally lightweight. It does not replace the standards
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:51:checklists and does not scan markdown prose. These remain manual review gates:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:52:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:53:- exact visual header shape beyond the marker-level checks above;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:54:- naming conventions;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:55:- comment density and WHY-vs-WHAT comment quality;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:56:- KISS/DRY/SOLID judgment;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:57:- JavaScript `module.exports` versus plugin ESM default-export decisions;
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:58:- TypeScript package-boundary decisions such as NodeNext ESM versus root
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:59:  CommonJS defaults.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:60:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:61:### Severity model
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:62:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:63:- **ERROR**: parse/integrity findings (`COMMON-*`, `JSON-*`, `JSONC-*`) in active paths.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:64:- **WARN**: style findings (`JS-*`, `TS-*`, `PY-*`, `SH-*`) by default.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:65:- **Context-aware advisory downgrade**: any finding under archival/contextual paths is downgraded to `WARN`:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:66:  - `z_archive`, `scratch`, `memory`, `research`, `context`, `assets`, `examples`, `fixtures`, and test-heavy paths.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:67:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:68:## 4. USAGE
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:69:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:70:```bash
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:71:python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py --root .opencode
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:72:```
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:73:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:74:Strict CI mode:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:75:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:76:```bash
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:77:python3 .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/verify_alignment_drift.py --root .opencode --fail-on-warn
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:78:```
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:79:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:80:Notes:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:81:- `--root` is repeatable; when omitted, current directory is scanned.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:82:- Files are deduplicated by realpath when repeated/overlapping roots are provided.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:83:- Output includes both rule id and severity (`[RULE] [ERROR|WARN]`).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:84:- Exit code `0` means no blocking findings (warnings are non-blocking by default).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:85:- Exit code `1` means one or more errors were found, or warnings were found with `--fail-on-warn`.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:86:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:87:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:88:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:89:## 5. RELATED RESOURCES
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/shared/alignment-verification-automation.md:90:
