    51	Expected result: the command lists the source files summarized below.
    52	
    53	**Step 3: Verify changes.**
    54	
    55	Run individual scripts from the repository root with the documented arguments.
    56	
    57	---
    58	
    59	## 3. FEATURES
    60	
    61	| Feature | What It Does |
    62	|---|---|
    63	| Folder boundary | Documents direct code files under `assets/scripts`. |
    64	| sk-code alignment | Points reviewers at OpenCode naming, header, error-handling, and type-discipline checks. |
    65	| Verification handoff | Records the expected owner and audit packet for follow-up work. |
    66	
    67	---
    68	
    69	## 4. STRUCTURE
    70	
    71	| Path | Purpose |
    72	|---|---|
    73	| `test_verify_alignment_drift.py` | Unit-style coverage for alignment drift file discovery, language checks, severity behavior, and CLI exit codes. |
    74	| `verify_alignment_drift.py` | Recurring read-only alignment verifier for TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, shell, JSON, and JSONC files. |
    75	| `verify_stack_folders.py` | Verifies code-opencode language reference folders match the known language set and flags missing or orphan folders. |
    76	
    77	---
    78	
    79	## 5. CONFIGURATION
    80	
    81	| Setting | Default | Purpose |
    82	|---|---|---|
    83	| sk-code surface | OPENCODE | Applies OpenCode TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, Shell, and config conventions. |
    84	| README scope | Direct folder | This file documents this folder, not sibling folders. |
    85	
    86	---
    87	
    88	## 6. USAGE EXAMPLES
    89	
    90	**Audit this folder**
    91	
    92	```text
    93	User request: Check .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts for sk-code and README coverage.
    94	Skill routing: sk-code plus sk-doc.
    95	Expected output: Findings recorded in the current refinement and release-alignment review.
    96	```
    97	
    98	---
    99	
   100	## 7. TROUBLESHOOTING
   101	
   102	| What You See | Cause | Fix |
   103	|---|---|---|
   104	| README appears stale | Source files changed after this audit | Refresh the structure table and rerun the current release-alignment README remediation check. |
