     9	---
    10	
    11	<!-- Keywords: code-review, review, findings-first, pull-request, security-review, quality-gate, stack-agnostic, baseline-surface, sk-code -->
    12	
    13	# code-review Mode - Stack-Agnostic Findings-First Review
    14	
    15	Universal findings-first review baseline paired with `sk-code` surface standards evidence for the detected code surface.
    16	
    17	## 1. WHEN TO USE
    18	
    19	### Activation Triggers
    20	
    21	Use the `code-review` mode (of the sk-code family) when:
    22	- A user asks for code review, PR review, quality gate, or merge readiness.
    23	- A workflow dispatches `@review` for pre-commit or gate validation.
    24	- A user requests security/correctness risk analysis before merge.
    25	- A user wants severity-ranked findings with file:line evidence.
    26	
    27	### Keyword Triggers
    28	
    29	`review`, `code review`, `pr review`, `audit`, `security review`, `quality gate`, `request changes`, `findings`, `blocking issues`, `merge readiness`
    30	
    31	### Use Cases
    32	
    33	1. Review-only pass: findings-first output with no code edits.
    34	2. Gate validation: score + pass/fail recommendation for orchestrated workflows.
    35	3. Focused risk pass: security, concurrency, correctness, or removal-focused review.
    36	
    37	### When NOT to Use
    38	
    39	- Feature implementation without review intent; use the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`).
    40	- Pure documentation editing where code behavior is not being assessed.
    41	- Git-only workflow tasks (branching, rebasing, commit hygiene) without code-quality evaluation intent.
    42	- Applying review fixes after findings are accepted; use the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`).
    43	- Author-side quality gates before review; use `code-quality`.
    44	- Root-cause debugging; use the surface's `workflow-debug.md` doctrine.
    45	- Verification evidence collection; use the surface's `workflow-verify.md` doctrine.
    46	
    47	---
    48	
    49	## 2. SMART ROUTING
    50	
    51	
    52	### Primary Detection Signal
    53	
    54	Review behavior follows a baseline+surface-evidence model:
    55	
    56	- Baseline (always): the `code-review` mode (of the sk-code family) findings-first doctrine.
    57	- Surface standards evidence (when available): `sk-code` detected surface resources.
    58	- Unknown surfaces: review against baseline security/correctness only and disclose uncertainty.
    59	
    60	### Phase Detection
    61	
    62	```text
    63	TASK CONTEXT
    64	    |
    65	    +- STEP 0: Load the `code-review` mode baseline + `sk-code` surface evidence. The dispatcher / agent assembling the code-review prompt MUST prepend `CODE-REVIEW\n\n` as the first two lines of the rendered prompt before the reviewer LLM sees it. Reference resources stay unchanged.
    66	    +- STEP 1: Score intents (top-2 when ambiguity delta <= 1.0)
    67	    +- Phase 1: Scope and baseline checks
    68	    +- Phase 2: Overlay alignment
    69	    +- Phase 3: Findings-first analysis
    70	    +- Phase 4: Output contract and next action
    71	```
    72	
    73	### Resource Domains
    74	
    75	The router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies weighted intent scoring.
    76	
    77	Knowledge is organized by domain mapping:
    78	
    79	```text
    80	references/review-core.md
    81	references/review-ux-single-pass.md
    82	references/pr-state-dedup.md
    83	references/quick-reference.md
    84	assets/*_checklist.md
    85	assets/removal-plan.md
    86	```
    87	
    88	- `references/review-core.md` for shared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.
    89	- `references/review-ux-single-pass.md` for interactive single-pass review behavior.
    90	- `references/quick-reference.md` for the lightweight routing index across review references.
    91	- `references/` for shared doctrine, UX behavior, and PR-state dedup.
    92	- `assets/` for security, quality, completeness, SOLID, test-quality, and removal checklists.
    93	
    94	### Resource Loading Levels
    95	
    96	| Level | When to Load | Resources |
    97	| --- | --- | --- |
    98	| ALWAYS | Every invocation, including security/correctness reviews | `references/review-core.md`, `references/review-ux-single-pass.md`, `assets/security-checklist.md`, `assets/code-quality-checklist.md`, `assets/fix-completeness-checklist.md` |
    99	| CONDITIONAL | Intent score indicates need | `assets/solid-checklist.md`, `assets/code-quality-checklist.md`, `assets/removal-plan.md`, `assets/test-quality-checklist.md` |
   100	| CONDITIONAL | `CORE` / `COMPLETENESS` / `PR_STATE` / `SETUP` intents | `references/review-core.md`, `references/review-ux-single-pass.md`, `assets/fix-completeness-checklist.md`, `references/pr-state-dedup.md`, `references/quick-reference.md` |
   101	| ON_DEMAND | Explicit deep-dive request | Full mapped reference set |
   102	
   103	### Precedence Matrix
   104	
   105	| Rule Type | Source of Truth | Behavior |
   106	| --- | --- | --- |
   107	| Security/correctness minimums | `code-review` mode baseline | Always enforced; never relaxed by surface guidance |
   108	| Surface style/process conventions | `sk-code` detected surface | Surface guidance overrides baseline generic style/process advice |
   109	| Verification/build/test commands | `sk-code` detected surface | Surface commands are authoritative for the detected surface |
   110	| Ambiguous conflicts | Escalation | Ask for clarification; do not guess |
   111	
   112	### Unknown Fallback Checklist
   113	
   114	If intent/stack detection is unclear, request:
   115	
   116	1. Review target scope (full diff, staged files, commit range, or explicit file list).
   117	2. Primary risk class (security, correctness, performance, maintainability).
   118	3. Architecture lens priority (KISS/DRY/SOLID strict or optional).
   119	4. Stack/context (system code, web/frontend, or other/full-stack).
   120	5. Desired output mode (findings-only or findings + gated fix follow-up).
   121	
   122	### Smart Router Pseudocode
   123	
   124	```python
   125	import re
   126	from pathlib import Path
   127	
   128	SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent
   129	# Discover resources recursively across references and assets.
   130	RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / "references", SKILL_ROOT / "assets")
   131	DEFAULT_RESOURCES = [
   132	    "references/review-core.md",
   133	    "references/review-ux-single-pass.md",
   134	    "assets/security-checklist.md",
   135	    "assets/code-quality-checklist.md",
   136	    "assets/fix-completeness-checklist.md",
   137	]
   138	
   139	INTENT_SIGNALS = {
   140	    "SECURITY": {"weight": 5, "keywords": ["security", "auth", "injection", "vulnerability", "race"]},
   141	    "QUALITY": {"weight": 4, "keywords": ["correctness", "bug", "regression", "performance", "boundary", "contract", "breaking change", "backward compatible", "compatibility"]},
   142	    "KISS": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["kiss", "simple", "simplicity", "over-engineer", "overengineering"]},
   143	    "DRY": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["dry", "duplication", "duplicate", "copy-paste", "repeated logic"]},
   144	    "SOLID": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["solid", "architecture", "design", "coupling", "cohesion", "module", "adapter", "interface", "abstraction", "responsibility", "dependency", "boundary"]},
   145	    "REMOVAL": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["remove", "dead code", "cleanup", "deprecate"]},
   146	    "TESTING": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["test", "tests", "testing", "coverage", "assertion", "mock", "stub", "fixture", "test quality", "brittle"]},
   147	    "CORE": {"weight": 2, "keywords": ["review doctrine", "review standards", "review baseline", "single pass", "single-pass", "interactive review", "one-pass review"]},
   148	    "COMPLETENESS": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["fix completeness", "incomplete fix", "partial fix", "complete the fix", "all call sites", "leftover", "half-done"]},
   149	    "PR_STATE": {"weight": 3, "keywords": ["pr state", "pull request state", "dedup", "deduplicate", "duplicate finding", "already flagged", "prior comment", "repeated finding"]},
   150	    "SETUP": {"weight": 2, "keywords": ["quick reference", "review setup", "how to review", "review workflow", "review cheat sheet"]},
   151	}
   152	
   153	RESOURCE_MAP = {
   154	    "SECURITY": ["assets/security-checklist.md"],
   155	    "QUALITY": ["assets/code-quality-checklist.md"],
   156	    "KISS": ["assets/code-quality-checklist.md"],
   157	    "DRY": ["assets/code-quality-checklist.md"],
   158	    "SOLID": ["assets/solid-checklist.md"],
   159	    "REMOVAL": ["assets/removal-plan.md"],
   160	    "TESTING": ["assets/test-quality-checklist.md"],
   161	    "CORE": ["references/review-core.md", "references/review-ux-single-pass.md"],
   162	    "COMPLETENESS": ["assets/fix-completeness-checklist.md"],
   163	    "PR_STATE": ["references/pr-state-dedup.md"],
   164	    "SETUP": ["references/quick-reference.md"],
   165	}
   166	
   167	ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS = ["deep review", "full review", "all checks", "comprehensive", "flag false positives", "blocking regressions", "list findings", "read-only only", "underrepresented", "scope correctly"]
   168	UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [
   169	    "Confirm review scope (diff/staged/files/commit range)",
   170	    "Confirm risk priority (security/correctness/performance/maintainability/test quality/contract safety)",
   171	    "Confirm architecture lens (KISS/DRY/SOLID required or optional)",
   172	    "Confirm stack context (system-code/web/full-stack)",
   173	    "Confirm findings-only vs findings+fix follow-up",
   174	]
   175	
   176	def _task_text(task) -> str:
   177	    return " ".join([
   178	        str(getattr(task, "text", "")),
   179	        str(getattr(task, "query", "")),
   180	        str(getattr(task, "description", "")),
   181	        " ".join(getattr(task, "keywords", []) or []),
   182	    ]).lower()
   183	
   184	def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:
   185	    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()
   186	    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)
   187	    if resolved.suffix.lower() != ".md":
   188	        raise ValueError(f"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}")
   189	    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()
   190	

