   393	---
   394	
   395	## 4. RULES
   396	
   397	### ✅ ALWAYS
   398	
   399	- Keep findings first; summaries follow findings.
   400	- Enforce baseline security/correctness minimums regardless of surface.
   401	- Include file:line evidence for actionable findings.
   402	- State assumptions when evidence is incomplete.
   403	- Identify `sk-code` surface evidence used for standards alignment.
   404	
   405	### ⛔ NEVER
   406	
   407	- Override surface-specific conventions with generic baseline style preferences.
   408	- Approve code with unaddressed P0 security/correctness defects.
   409	- Produce vague findings without concrete evidence.
   410	- Mix unrelated cleanup into targeted fix recommendations.
   411	- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.
   412	
   413	### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF
   414	
   415	- Surface detection is ambiguous and affects standards or verification commands.
   416	- Baseline and surface guidance conflict in a non-deterministic way.
   417	- Large diff size prevents reliable severity assignment without narrowed scope.
   418	- Requested remediation exceeds review scope and becomes architecture redesign.
   419	
