   469	
   470	## 9. PR-STATE EFFICIENCY GATES
   471	
   472	### 9.1 M-1: PR-State Content-Hash Dedup
   473	
   474	Prevents redundant re-reviews when a PR has not changed since the last review.
   475	
   476	**Signature computation:**
   477	```
   478	diff_content_hash = sha256(git diff <base-ref>...HEAD)
   479	signature         = sha256(commit_subject + "\u001f" + diff_content_hash)
   480	```
   481	Where `commit_subject` is the first line of `git log <base-ref>...HEAD --format=%s` (latest commit subject).
   482	
   483	**Cache storage:**
   484	- Path: `.opencode/.code-review-cache/<repo-ref>.jsonl`
   485	- `<repo-ref>` is computed as `sha256(git remote get-url origin).slice(0, 12)`
   486	- Each line is a JSON object: `{"signature": "<sha256-hex>", "timestamp": "<ISO-8601>", "prev_sha": "<commit-sha>"}`
   487	- Retention: keep last **100 entries** per repo-ref, prune older entries on write
   488	
   489	**Skip behavior:**
   490	When the current signature matches a prior cache entry, the review emits:
   491	```
   492	Review status: COMMENTED (no changes since last review at <prev_sha>)
   493	```
   494	No full review analysis runs. Automation may treat `COMMENTED` as a pass (no new findings).
   495	
   496	**Cache write:** After each full review completes, write the current signature + timestamp + HEAD SHA to the cache file.
   497	
   498	### 9.2 M-2: Opt-In Minimum Evidence Gate
   499	
   500	Skips full review for trivially small diffs to save compute, with a conservative taxonomy that **never skips** high-risk changes.
   501	
   502	**Enable gate:**
   503	```bash
   504	export SK_CODE_REVIEW_MIN_CHANGED_LINES=50  # >0 enables; default 0 = disabled
   505	```
   506	
   507	**Changed-line counting command:**
   508	```bash
   509	git diff --numstat <base-ref>...HEAD | awk '{added+=$1; removed+=$2} END {print added+removed}'
   510	```
   511	
   512	**Conservative skip taxonomy — NEVER skip when diff touches:**
   513	
   514	| Risk Class | Path/File Patterns | Rationale |
   515	|---|---|---|
   516	| Security / Authentication / Authorization | `auth*`, `*-auth-*`, `*permission*`, `*credential*`, `*token*`, `*secret*`, `*oauth*`, `*sso*`, `*login*`, `*session*` | Compromised auth defeats everything |
   517	| Config files | `*.config.*`, `*config*.json`, `*config*.yaml`, `*config*.toml`, `*.env*`, `*.ini`, `*.cfg` | One-line config change can break production |
   518	| Persistence | `*.sql`, `*migration*`, `*schema*`, `*db*.ts`, `*repository*`, paths under `/db/` or `/migrations/` | Schema changes risk data loss |
   519	| Dependency manifests | `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, `pyproject.toml`, `poetry.lock`, `requirements.txt`, `*.lock`, `Gemfile`, `Gemfile.lock` | Transitive dependency changes are high-risk |
   520	| Sandboxing / Subprocess | `*sandbox*`, `*subprocess*`, `*exec*`, `*spawn*`, `*eval*` | Arbitrary code execution boundaries |
   521	| Public-facing responses | `*.handler.ts`, `*-api*`, `*-route*`, `*-controller*`, paths under `/handlers/`, `/routes/`, `/api/` | User-visible behavior changes |
   522	
   523	**Skip behavior:**
   524	When `SK_CODE_REVIEW_MIN_CHANGED_LINES > 0`, total changed lines < threshold, AND no sensitive paths are touched:
   525	```
   526	Review status: COMMENTED (skipped: diff below evidence threshold of N lines, no sensitive paths touched)
   527	```
   528	If sensitive paths ARE touched, the full review runs regardless of line count.
   529	
   530	**Gate is ALWAYS opt-in.** Without `SK_CODE_REVIEW_MIN_CHANGED_LINES` set, M-2 has zero effect — all diffs receive full reviews.
   531	
   532	### 9.3 SK_CODE_REVIEW_DEPTH (opt-in depth alias)
   533	
   534	`SK_CODE_REVIEW_DEPTH=lite|full|ultra` is an optional environment variable the **reviewing agent honors** (resolved env > config > default) — exactly like the §9.2 `SK_CODE_REVIEW_MIN_CHANGED_LINES` gate. Both are skill guidance the reviewer reads and applies in-loop, not a separate compiled dispatcher; this alias only NAMES and PERSISTS an already-existing routing behavior, adds no new tier, and relaxes no floor:
   535	
   536	- `full` (default / unset): the normal ALWAYS + CONDITIONAL + ON_DEMAND routing.
   537	- `ultra`: bias intent selection toward the existing `ON_DEMAND` reference set (the deep-dive tier) for the session, so a reviewer does not have to repeat "comprehensive / full review" each time.
   538	- `lite`: maps to the existing M-2 conservative skip (§9.2) — it NEVER lowers the ALWAYS tier, the baseline security/correctness minimums, or the P0/P1/P2 contract. It cannot skip a review on a sensitive path (auth/config/persistence/deps/sandbox/public-response), exactly as M-2 already enforces.
   539	
   540	The depth alias is advisory routing only; it must never be read as permission to relax a floor.
   541	
