.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:38:### Numeric Severity Calibration
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:39:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:40:Numeric scores are advisory context, not the gate. A reviewer may add an optional `riskScore` to a finding and adjust it by `+/-2` for local context such as exploitability, blast radius, user impact, confidence, or proven containment. The merge/block decision remains the severity contract above: `P0` blocks, `P1` requires remediation, and `P2` is advisory. Do not adopt `score>=4` or any numeric threshold as a blocker.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:41:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:42:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:43:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:44:## 3. EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:45:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:46:- Every `P0` and `P1` finding must include a concrete `file:line` citation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:47:- Evidence must tie the finding to observed code behavior, not just a general concern.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:48:- `P2` findings should still include specific evidence when available, even if impact is advisory.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:49:- If evidence is incomplete, state the assumption and why the risk still matters.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:50:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:51:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:52:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:53:## 4. FINDINGS OUTPUT ORDERING
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:54:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:55:- Present findings before summary or praise sections.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:56:- Order findings by severity first: `P0`, then `P1`, then `P2`.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:57:- Keep ordering stable within a severity bucket by impact and confidence.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:58:- Separate required fixes from optional suggestions so merge decisions stay clear.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:59:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:60:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:61:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:62:## 5. BASELINE + SURFACE PRECEDENCE
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:63:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:64:Apply this skill as the baseline first, then pair it with `sk-code` surface evidence when available:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:65:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:66:- Detected code surface -> `sk-code:code-webflow` or `sk-code:code-opencode`; unsupported or unclear surfaces -> `sk-code:unknown`
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:67:- Unclear surfaces -> baseline-only plus explicit uncertainty
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:68:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:69:Precedence rules:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:70:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:71:- Baseline security and correctness minimums are always enforced.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:72:- Surface style, process, build, and test conventions override generic baseline guidance.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:73:- Unclear conflicts must be escalated rather than guessed.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:74:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:75:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:76:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:77:## 6. BASELINE CHECK FAMILIES
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:78:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:79:Mandatory baseline families:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:80:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:81:- Correctness minimums: regression risk, contract safety, spec mismatch, destructive side effects, and boundary handling.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:82:- Security minimums: auth and authorization gaps, injection exposure, unsafe secrets handling, privilege misuse, and reliability risks with security impact.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:83:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:84:These minimums cannot be relaxed by surface guidance.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:85:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:86:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:87:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:88:## 7. FINDING SCHEMA
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:89:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:90:Each finding should provide:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:91:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:92:| Field | Requirement |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:93:| --- | --- |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:94:| `id` | Stable label within the review report, such as `P1-001` |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:95:| `severity` | One of `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:96:| `title` | Short, risk-oriented summary |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:97:| `file` | Primary `path:line` location |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:98:| `evidence` | Plain-language explanation tied to observed code |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:99:| `findingClass` | One of `instance-only`, `class-of-bug`, `cross-consumer`, `algorithmic`, `matrix/evidence`, or `test-isolation` |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:100:| `scopeProof` | Grep/test/audit evidence that the recommendation covers same-class sites and consumers, or proves the finding is instance-only |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:101:| `affectedSurfaceHints` | Optional string array of producer/consumer surfaces the fix should address; recommended for actionable findings, required for cross-consumer findings. Use free-form short strings, max about 5 entries. Optional for instance-only findings. |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:102:| `riskScore` | Optional advisory number for relative risk calibration; never gating and never a substitute for `severity` |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:103:| `recommendation` | Specific, scope-proportional fix or follow-up |
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:104:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:105:Suggested shape:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:106:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:107:```markdown
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:108:### P1-001 [P1] Missing authorization check
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:109:- File: path/to/file.ts:42
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:110:- Evidence: Request handling reaches the write path before role validation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:111:- Finding class: cross-consumer
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:112:- Scope proof: `rg -n "permission guard|write path" path/to` shows the write handler is the only unchecked consumer.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:113:- Affected surface hints: ["request handler", "write path", "permission guard"]
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:114:- riskScore: 6 (advisory only)
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:115:- Recommendation: Enforce the existing permission guard before mutation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:116:```
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:117:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:118:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:119:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:120:## 8. RELATED RESOURCES
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:121:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:122:- [review-ux-single-pass.md](./review-ux-single-pass.md) - Interactive single-pass report flow and next-step prompts.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:123:- [quick-reference.md](./quick-reference.md) - Lightweight index across baseline review references.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:124:- [security-checklist.md](../assets/security-checklist.md) - Security and reliability checks.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:125:- [code-quality-checklist.md](../assets/code-quality-checklist.md) - Correctness, KISS, DRY, and maintainability checks.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:126:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md:127:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:1:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:2:title: Review UX - Single Pass
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:3:description: Interactive single-pass review behavior for human-facing review sessions.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:4:trigger_phrases:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:5:  - "single pass review ux"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:6:  - "review first implement second"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:7:  - "next step options after findings"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:8:  - "pre commit review guidance"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:9:importance_tier: normal
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:10:contextType: implementation
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:11:version: 1.5.0.5
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:12:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:13:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:14:# Review UX - Single Pass
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:15:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:16:Interactive behavior for a one-pass review where findings are reported first and the human chooses what happens next.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:17:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:18:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:19:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:20:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:21:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:22:Interactive single-pass review behavior for human-facing review sessions.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:23:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:24:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:25:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:26:## 2. HUMAN INTERACTION BEHAVIOR
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:27:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:28:- Review first, implement second.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:29:- After publishing findings, ask the user what to do next before writing code.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:30:- Keep the prompt concrete and mode-aware; do not ask open-ended process questions unless scope is unclear.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:31:- If no blocking findings exist, still offer explicit next-step choices instead of assuming implementation work.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:32:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:33:Recommended next-step options:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:34:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:35:1. Fix all findings
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:36:2. Fix `P0` and `P1` only
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:37:3. Fix selected findings
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:38:4. No implementation changes
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:39:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:40:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:41:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:42:## 3. REPORT FLOW
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:43:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:44:Use this flow for interactive review responses:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:45:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:46:1. State what was reviewed and the scope source (`git diff`, staged diff, file list, or commit range).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:47:2. Publish findings ordered by severity.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:48:3. Summarize merge posture or risk level briefly.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:49:4. Ask the user what to do next.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:50:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:51:If no diff is present, report:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:52:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:53:- What was checked
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:54:- That no diff was found
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:55:- A concrete follow-up choice: staged changes only, specific commit/range, or selected files
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:56:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:57:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:58:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:59:## 4. MODE-SPECIFIC PRESENTATION
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:60:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:61:Choose the lightest presentation that fits the request:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:62:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:63:- Findings-only: list the issues with evidence and stop after the next-step prompt.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:64:- Findings + gate recommendation: include `APPROVE`, `REQUEST_CHANGES`, or `COMMENT` after the findings.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:65:- Findings + fix follow-up options: present the review, then offer concrete remediation choices without starting implementation automatically.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:66:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:67:Presentation rules:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:68:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:69:- Keep findings ahead of summary sections.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:70:- Use plain-language impact statements.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:71:- Distinguish optional advice clearly from required fixes.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:72:- Acknowledge notable strengths briefly after the required findings, not before them.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:73:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:74:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:75:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:76:## 5. PR AND PRE-COMMIT GUIDANCE
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:77:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:78:For PR review:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:79:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:80:- Check for scope drift and call out unrelated changes that should be split.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:81:- Assess contract and backward-compatibility risk for externally visible changes.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:82:- Tie the overall recommendation to merge readiness.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:83:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:84:For pre-commit or staged review:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:85:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:86:- Focus on the staged diff or requested file set.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:87:- Prioritize the fastest blocking feedback first.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:88:- Keep remediation suggestions small and easy to apply before commit.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:89:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:90:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:91:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:92:## 6. RELATED RESOURCES
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:93:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:94:- [review-core.md](./review-core.md) - Shared doctrine used by both interactive and deep review modes.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:95:- [quick-reference.md](./quick-reference.md) - Lightweight index for the review reference set.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:96:- [test-quality-checklist.md](../assets/test-quality-checklist.md) - Test quality and coverage checks for changed tests.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:97:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:98:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-ux-single-pass.md:99:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:1:---
