.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:3:description: Structured risk checklist for security vulnerabilities, runtime reliability issues, and concurrent-behavior defects.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:4:trigger_phrases:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:5:  - "security review minimums"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:6:  - "input output safety checks"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:7:  - "authn authz review checklist"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:8:  - "secrets and privacy review"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:9:  - "concurrency race condition review"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:10:  - "dependency supply chain audit"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:11:importance_tier: normal
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:12:contextType: implementation
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:13:version: 1.5.0.9
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:14:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:15:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:16:# Security and Reliability Checklist
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:17:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:18:Structured risk checklist for security vulnerabilities, runtime reliability issues, and concurrent-behavior defects.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:19:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:20:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:21:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:22:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:23:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:24:### Purpose
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:25:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:26:Help reviewers prioritize exploitability and business impact, not just code style.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:27:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:28:### Usage
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:29:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:30:Apply on security-relevant diffs; classify each finding by exploitability and business impact, and cite file:line evidence.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:31:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:32:### Core Principle
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:33:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:34:When impact is unclear, prefer conservative classification and state uncertainty explicitly.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:35:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:36:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:37:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:38:## 2. INPUT/OUTPUT SAFETY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:39:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:40:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:41:- XSS via unsafe HTML rendering or template interpolation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:42:- SQL/NoSQL/command injection via string concatenation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:43:- SSRF through unvalidated user-controlled URLs.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:44:- Path traversal from unchecked path input (`../`).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:45:- Prototype pollution from unsafe object merge operations.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:46:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:47:Review prompts:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:48:- "What untrusted input reaches this sink?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:49:- "Is validation context-aware for this output channel?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:50:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:51:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:52:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:53:## 3. AUTHENTICATION AND AUTHORIZATION
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:54:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:55:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:56:- Missing auth guards on newly added entry points.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:57:- Missing ownership/tenant checks for read/write actions.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:58:- Trust in client-supplied role flags or user IDs.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:59:- IDOR patterns where entity IDs are accepted without authorization.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:60:- Weak token/session validation (`exp`, `iss`, `aud`, algorithm checks).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:61:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:62:High-impact rule: any missing authz control on data mutation is at least P1 and often P0.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:63:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:64:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:65:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:66:## 4. SECRETS AND PRIVACY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:67:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:68:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:69:- Hardcoded credentials, API keys, tokens, private keys.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:70:- Sensitive logs exposing PII or operational secrets.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:71:- Internal stack traces or environment details in user-facing errors.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:72:- Client-side exposure of server-only configuration values.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:73:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:74:Quick command ideas:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:75:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:76:```bash
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:77:rg -n -i "api[_-]?key|secret|token|password|BEGIN .* PRIVATE KEY"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:78:```
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:79:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:80:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:81:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:82:## 5. RUNTIME RELIABILITY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:83:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:84:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:85:- Missing timeouts/retries for network dependencies.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:86:- Unbounded loops, recursion, or memory growth.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:87:- Blocking I/O on hot request paths.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:88:- Regex patterns vulnerable to catastrophic backtracking (ReDoS).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:89:- Missing idempotency keys for retry-prone write operations.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:90:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:91:Review prompt:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:92:- "What fails under load or partial network failure?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:93:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:94:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:95:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:96:## 6. CONCURRENCY AND RACE CONDITIONS
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:97:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:98:Flag patterns:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:99:- Check-then-act without atomicity.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:100:- Read-modify-write on shared state without lock/transaction.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:101:- File/system operations split into non-atomic checks and actions.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:102:- Counter updates without atomic increment semantics.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:103:- Distributed coordination without lock/lease guarantees.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:104:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:105:Examples:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:106:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:107:```text
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:108:if not exists(key):
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:109:    create(key)
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:110:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:111:value = get(key)
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:112:value += 1
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:113:set(key, value)
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:114:```
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:115:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:116:Reviewer questions:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:117:- "What happens if two requests hit this path at the same time?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:118:- "Is this update atomic across all failure modes?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:119:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:120:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:121:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:122:## 7. RATE LIMITING AND ABUSE PREVENTION
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:123:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:124:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:125:- Missing rate limits on authentication endpoints (login, signup, password reset).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:126:- Unthrottled API endpoints accepting expensive operations.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:127:- Missing abuse vectors: account enumeration, credential stuffing, brute force.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:128:- Lack of per-user or per-IP request budgets on public-facing routes.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:129:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:130:Review prompt:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:131:- "What stops an attacker from calling this endpoint 10,000 times per second?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:132:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:133:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:134:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:135:## 8. CONTENT SECURITY POLICY AND HEADERS
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:136:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:137:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:138:- Missing or overly permissive CSP headers (`unsafe-inline`, `unsafe-eval`, wildcard sources).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:139:- Missing security headers: `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:140:- CORS misconfiguration: wildcard origins, credentials with broad origins.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:141:- Missing `SameSite` attribute on sensitive cookies.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:142:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:143:Review prompt:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:144:- "Could an attacker embed, frame, or inject scripts into this page?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:145:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:146:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:147:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:148:## 9. DEPENDENCY AND SUPPLY CHAIN SECURITY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:149:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:150:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:151:- Known vulnerabilities in dependencies (`npm audit`, `pip-audit`, `cargo audit`).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:152:- Unpinned or loosely pinned dependency versions (major version ranges).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:153:- Dependencies with no maintainer activity or known compromises.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:154:- Post-install scripts in untrusted packages.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:155:- Lock file integrity (committed and consistent with manifest).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:156:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:157:Review prompt:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:158:- "Are all dependencies pinned, audited, and from trusted sources?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:159:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:160:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:161:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:162:## 10. AUDIT LOGGING AND OBSERVABILITY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:163:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:164:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:165:- Missing audit logs for security-sensitive operations (auth, permission changes, data deletion).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:166:- Insufficient context in logs (who, what, when, from where).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:167:- Logging sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII) in plain text.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:168:- Missing alerting for anomalous patterns (repeated auth failures, privilege escalation).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:169:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:170:Review prompt:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:171:- "If this action were abused, would we know about it from the logs?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:172:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:173:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:174:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:175:## 11. PRIVACY AND DATA HANDLING
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:176:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:177:Check for:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:178:- PII stored without encryption at rest or purpose limitation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:179:- Missing data retention policies or deletion mechanisms.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:180:- Cross-border data transfer without adequate safeguards.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:181:- Excessive data collection beyond stated purpose.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:182:- Missing consent mechanisms for user data processing.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:183:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:184:Review prompt:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:185:- "Does this code collect, store, or transmit personal data - and is that justified and protected?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:186:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:187:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:188:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/security-checklist.md:189:## 12. RELATED RESOURCES
