.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:1:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:2:title: Test Quality Checklist
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:3:description: Test adequacy, coverage quality, and anti-pattern detection checklist for identifying unreliable or misleading test suites.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:4:trigger_phrases:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:5:  - "test quality review checklist"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:6:  - "tests that cannot fail"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:7:  - "test smell detection"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:8:  - "coverage quality assessment"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:9:  - "test pyramid awareness"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:10:importance_tier: normal
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:11:contextType: implementation
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:12:version: 1.5.0.7
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:13:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:14:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:15:# Test Quality Checklist
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:16:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:17:Test adequacy, coverage quality, and anti-pattern detection checklist for identifying unreliable or misleading test suites.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:18:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:19:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:20:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:21:## 1. OVERVIEW
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:22:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:23:### Purpose
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:24:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:25:Provide a systematic pass for test defects that reduce confidence in code correctness or mask regressions.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:26:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:27:### Usage
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:28:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:29:Apply when the diff changes tests; check each item against the test diff and flag false-confidence patterns that mask regressions.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:30:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:31:### Core Principle
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:32:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:33:Tests that cannot fail are worse than no tests. They create false confidence and hide real defects.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:34:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:35:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:36:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:37:## 2. COVERAGE QUALITY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:38:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:39:Flag:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:40:- Test functions that execute code paths without any assertions (assertion-free execution).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:41:- Test suites covering only happy-path scenarios with no error or edge case validation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:42:- Changed behavior that lacks a corresponding test update or addition.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:43:- New public API surface introduced without any test coverage.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:44:- Snapshot or golden-file tests that auto-pass because the baseline was never updated after behavior changes.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:45:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:46:Review prompts:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:47:- "Does every test function contain at least one meaningful assertion?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:48:- "Are failure modes and boundary conditions tested alongside the happy path?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:49:- "Do the tests cover the behavior that actually changed in this diff?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:50:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:51:Severity guidance:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:52:- P0 for assertion-free test functions (silently passing tests that verify nothing).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:53:- P1 for changed behavior with no corresponding test update.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:54:- P2 for missing edge case coverage on low-risk paths.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:55:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:56:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:57:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:58:## 3. TEST STRUCTURE AND CLARITY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:59:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:60:Flag:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:61:- Test functions missing clear Arrange/Act/Assert separation.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:62:- Test names that do not describe the scenario or expected outcome.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:63:- Magic values in test data without comments explaining their significance.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:64:- Multiple unrelated assertions in a single test function.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:65:- Test setup that obscures the behavior under test.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:66:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:67:Review prompts:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:68:- "Can a reader determine what this test validates from the name alone?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:69:- "Is the test data traceable to a specific requirement or edge case?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:70:- "Would a failure message from this test pinpoint the broken behavior?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:71:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:72:Severity guidance:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:73:- P2 default for structural clarity issues.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:74:- P1 if poor structure makes regression detection unreliable (for example, a multi-assertion test where early failures mask later ones).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:75:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:76:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:77:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:78:## 4. TEST INDEPENDENCE AND RELIABILITY
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:79:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:80:Flag:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:81:- Tests that depend on execution order or results from prior tests.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:82:- Shared mutable state between test functions without proper reset.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:83:- Tests that rely on wall-clock timing, network availability, or filesystem state.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:84:- Missing cleanup or teardown for resources created during test setup.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:85:- Tests that pass in isolation but fail when run with the full suite (or vice versa).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:86:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:87:Review prompts:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:88:- "Can each test run independently in any order and produce the same result?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:89:- "Does the test rely on external state that could change between runs?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:90:- "Is shared state properly isolated or reset between test functions?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:91:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:92:Severity guidance:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:93:- P1 for flaky tests or tests with execution-order dependencies.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:94:- P2 for missing teardown or cleanup that does not yet cause observed failures.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:95:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:96:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:97:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:98:## 5. TEST SMELL DETECTION
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:99:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:100:Flag:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:101:- Tests tightly coupled to implementation details (breaking on safe refactors).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:102:- Over-mocking that replaces the system under test with stubs, testing mock behavior instead of real behavior.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:103:- Conditional logic (if/else, try/catch) inside test functions that creates untested branches.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:104:- Catch blocks inside tests that swallow assertion failures and convert them to passing results.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:105:- Copy-paste duplication across test functions without shared helpers or parameterized tests.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:106:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:107:Review prompts:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:108:- "Would a safe refactor (rename, extract method) break this test without changing behavior?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:109:- "Is this test verifying real system behavior or just mock wiring?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:110:- "Does any catch block inside a test risk swallowing an assertion error?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:111:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:112:Severity guidance:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:113:- P0 for catch blocks that swallow assertion failures (tests that cannot fail).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:114:- P1 for over-mocking that makes the test unable to detect real defects.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:115:- P2 for implementation coupling or copy-paste duplication.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:116:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:117:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:118:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:119:## 6. TEST PYRAMID AWARENESS
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:120:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:121:Flag:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:122:- Unit tests that require database, network, or filesystem access (should be integration tests).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:123:- End-to-end tests for logic that can be validated at the unit level.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:124:- New external service calls or integrations introduced without integration test coverage.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:125:- Test suite dominated by one level (all unit, all E2E) with no balance.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:126:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:127:Review prompts:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:128:- "Is this test at the right level of the test pyramid for what it validates?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:129:- "Does a new external dependency have at least one integration-level test?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:130:- "Could this slow integration test be replaced by a faster unit test?"
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:131:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:132:Severity guidance:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:133:- P2 default for test-level misplacement.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:134:- P1 when wrong test level creates a confidence gap (for example, unit-testing an integration boundary without any integration test).
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:135:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:136:---
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:137:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:138:## 7. RELATED RESOURCES
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:139:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:140:- [quick-reference.md](../references/quick-reference.md) - Baseline review flow and severity output contract.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:141:- [code-quality-checklist.md](./code-quality-checklist.md) - Correctness, performance, KISS, and DRY checks.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:142:- [security-checklist.md](./security-checklist.md) - Security, authz, abuse, and privacy risk checks.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:143:- [solid-checklist.md](./solid-checklist.md) - SOLID (SRP/OCP/LSP/ISP/DIP) and architecture risk prompts.
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:144:
.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/assets/test-quality-checklist.md:145:Surface portability: pair this baseline with surface-specific test guidance from `sk-code`.

