     9	  - "instance only opt out"
    10	importance_tier: normal
    11	contextType: implementation
    12	version: 1.5.0.3
    13	---
    14	
    15	# Fix Completeness Checklist
    16	
    17	Checklist for turning a review finding into a complete fix that covers same-class producers, consumers, changed algorithms, matrix coverage, and hostile runtime state.
    18	
    19	## 1. OVERVIEW
    20	
    21	### Purpose
    22	
    23	Turn a review finding into a complete fix that covers same-class producers, consumers, changed algorithms, matrix coverage, and hostile runtime state, not just the one cited site.
    24	
    25	### Usage
    26	
    27	Use this when a finding becomes a fix: classify the finding, run the required inventories, and include the completion output before claiming done. A finding that meets the instance-only opt-out may use the narrow path with grep proof.
    28	
    29	---
    30	
    31	## 2. CLASSIFICATION
    32	
    33	State one class for every actionable finding:
    34	
    35	| Class | Use When | Required Proof |
    36	|-------|----------|----------------|
    37	| `instance-only` | One cited site and grep proves no siblings or consumers | Exact grep command and result |
    38	| `class-of-bug` | Same field/string/helper/error pattern can appear at sibling sites | Same-class producer inventory |
    39	| `cross-consumer` | Changed policy/helper/field is observed by other handlers, status, DB, docs, or tests | Consumer inventory |
    40	| `algorithmic` | Regex/parser/path/resolver/security logic is being changed | Invariant plus adversarial table tests |
    41	| `matrix/evidence` | Env/default/per-call, full/incremental, fresh/stale, root shape, runtime, or doc evidence axes exist | Full row table and SHA/range pin |
    42	| `test-isolation` | Env/global-state/singleton behavior is tested | Capture/restore proof and hostile env variant |
    43	
    44	### Instance-Only Opt-Out
    45	
    46	A finding may use the narrow fix path only when all are true:
    47	
    48	- It is not P0/P1 security, path, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, schema, persistence, or public-response behavior.
    49	- `rg` proves no same-class producer or consumer.
    50	- Verification is local and cheap: one focused test, one doc row, or one static audit command.
    51	- The fix response includes the exact command evidence for the opt-out.
    52	
    53	Otherwise, run the full fix completeness checklist.
    54	
    55	---
    56	
    57	## 3. REQUIRED INVENTORIES
    58	
    59	Same-class producers:
    60	
    61	```bash
    62	rg -n '<field|string|helper|literal|error-pattern>' <changed-files-or-module>
    63	rg -n 'errors\.push|warnings\.push|throw new Error|JSON.stringify|return \{.*error|message:' <changed-files-or-module>
    64	```
    65	
    66	Consumers:
    67	
    68	```bash
    69	rg -n '<changedSymbol>|<changedConstant>|<changedPublicField>' . --glob '*.ts' --glob '*.js' --glob '*.md'
    70	```
    71	
    72	Algorithm smell:
    73	
    74	```bash
    75	rg -n '\.replace\(|new RegExp|startsWith\(|includes\(|split\(' <changed-files>
    76	```
    77	
    78	Matrix/evidence:
    79	
    80	```bash
    81	rg -n 'it\.each|test\.each|describe\.each|requirement-id|source:' <changed-tests-and-packet-docs>
    82	git rev-parse --verify HEAD
    83	git diff --name-only <FIX_SHA>^..<FIX_SHA>
    84	```
    85	
    86	Hostile env/global state:
    87	
    88	```bash
    89	env <RELEVANT_ENV>=true <focused-test-command>
    90	env -u <RELEVANT_ENV> <focused-test-command>
    91	rg -n '<ENV_OR_GLOBAL_NAME>|original.*Env|afterEach|finally|reset\(' <changed-test-files>
    92	```
    93	
    94	---
    95	
    96	## 4. COMPLETION OUTPUT
    97	
    98	The fix response must include:
    99	
   100	- Changed files.
   101	- Finding class table.
   102	- Same-class producer inventory.
   103	- Consumer inventory.
   104	- Matrix rows added or verified.
   105	- Hostile env command when relevant.
   106	- Previously closed gates rechecked.
   107	- Intentionally unchanged siblings/consumers with evidence.
   108	
   109	---
   110	
   111	## 5. RELATED RESOURCES
   112	
   113	- [code-quality-checklist.md](./code-quality-checklist.md) - Correctness, performance, and maintainability checks.
   114	- [security-checklist.md](./security-checklist.md) - Security, authz, and reliability checks.
   115	- [../references/review-core.md](../references/review-core.md) - Findings-first review doctrine, severity model, and evidence rules.

