.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:57:| **Current authority** | Compiled manifests are present for seven hubs, but the runtime flag is off by default |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:59:| **Protected baseline** | `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, and `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs` remain frozen |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:60:| **Verification** | Per-hub serving status, route-gold parity, drift CI, canary evidence, and kill-switch drills |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:64:The recommended approach is the ordered P0-to-P4 program already ruled in `decision-record.md`. P0 makes the current flag and fallback state legible, separates drift from breakage in the harness, exposes serving status per hub, and removes or explicitly guards the resolver's dependency on a spec-tree path. P1 through P4 then add drift CI, a one-profile canary, data-driven eligibility, and a hub-by-hub global default change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:71:<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:72:## 2. QUALITY GATES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:77:- [ ] The fallback, drift-CI, observability, and migration contracts in `spec.md` and `decision-record.md` are treated as authoritative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:79:- [ ] The P2 canary environment profile and promotion owner are named.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:83:- [ ] P0 through P4 acceptance evidence is recorded without changing routing decisions.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:84:- [ ] The flag is documented before any default changes.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:85:- [ ] Drift is surfaced as drift, resolver breakage is surfaced as breakage, and per-hub authority is inspectable.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:87:- [ ] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` is exercised as the fleet-wide kill-switch after the staged cutover.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:89:<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:98:Observe, enforce, canary, derive, then cut over. Serving authority remains data-driven and fail-safe: runtime consumption is gated by the environment flag and per-hub eligibility, while a missing or stale manifest follows the legacy path defined by the authoritative contract.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:102:- **Environment contract**: documents the flag's current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:103:- **Serving-status probe**: reports `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, or `drifted` for each hub and separates expected degradation from execution failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:104:- **Drift CI**: recomputes live routing-input hashes and rejects stale manifests with a re-mint-required message.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:106:- **Canary profile**: enables the compiled path in one bounded environment while the repository default remains off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:118:flag + serving gate ---- disabled -----> legacy path + explicit status
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:121:compiled decision ---- parity gate ----> served only when legacy-equivalent
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:132:| `ENV-REFERENCE.md` | Source of truth for environment defaults | Document the flag, current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch | Documentation lint plus runtime default/override probes |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:133:| Verify harness | Treats fallback outcomes without enough cause detail | Add drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub status readout | Fresh, stale, missing, and broken fixtures |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:136:| Environment profiles | Repository default remains off | Enable one named canary profile only | Profile-specific flag assertion; all other profiles remain off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:138:| Hub directives and runtime defaults | Seven additive directives, default-off predicate | Stage P4 changes in lockstep, one hub at a time | Per-hub route parity, status readout, and `=0` rollback |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:146:- Record the resolver's current spec-tree dependency before choosing promotion or an explicit guard.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:154:### Phase 1: Setup (P0 governance and observability)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:156:- [ ] Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in the environment reference with default-off semantics and the explicit `=0` kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:157:- [ ] Extend the verify harness so drift-to-legacy is reported as degraded/expected while a broken resolver remains a hard failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:158:- [ ] Add the per-hub serving-status readout required by the observability contract.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:159:- [ ] Remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling by promoting the resolver to a stable runtime path; if the operator rejects promotion, add a loud path-integrity guard and document the residual drift source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:160:- [ ] Re-hash the three frozen scorer files before and after P0.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:163:### Phase 2: Implementation (P1 and P2 enforcement)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:165:- [ ] P1: add CI that recomputes each hub's live routing-input hash and compares it with the minted manifest digest.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:166:- [ ] P1: fail with `re-mint required: <hub>` whenever a routing input changes without a matching manifest update.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:167:- [ ] P2: select one environment profile and enable compiled routing only there; keep the repository default and all other profiles off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:168:- [ ] P2: record parity, serving-status, drift, and fallback evidence for the canary.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:169:- [ ] Re-hash the frozen scorer files after P1 and P2.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:170:- [ ] Rollback: disable the drift-CI job without removing its diagnostic command; unset the canary override or set it to `0`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:172:### Phase 3: Verification and Cutover (P3 and P4)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:174:- [ ] P3: implement one data-driven eligibility predicate using the valid-fresh-manifest rule from `decision-record.md`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:175:- [ ] P3: make both existing eligibility consumers derive from that predicate, retaining the old constants as a temporary rollback path until parity is proven.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:176:- [ ] P4: change the repository default in a staged hub order, updating the two runtime predicates and each hub directive in lockstep.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:177:- [ ] P4: after every hub, require route-gold parity, a `compiled-serving` status, clean fallback behavior, and unchanged scorer hashes before proceeding.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:178:- [ ] P4: exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch and retain per-hub manifest rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:179:- [ ] Rollback: stop at the first failed gate, set the flag to `0`, restore the affected hub's prior authority, and, if needed, restore the temporary hardcoded eligibility constants.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:184:<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->
