 succeeded in 0ms:
   238	### Scenario Acceptance Rules
   239	
   240	For each executed scenario, check:
   241	
   242	1. Preconditions were satisfied.
   243	2. Prompt and command sequence were executed as written.
   244	3. Expected signals are present.
   245	4. Evidence is complete and readable.
   246	5. Outcome rationale is explicit.
   247	
   248	Scenario verdict:
   249	- `PASS`: all acceptance checks true
   250	- `PARTIAL`: core behavior works but non-critical evidence or metadata is incomplete
   251	- `FAIL`: expected behavior missing, contradictory output, or critical check failed
   252	
   253	### Feature Verdict Rules
   254	
   255	- `PASS`: all mapped scenarios for feature are `PASS`
   256	- `PARTIAL`: at least one mapped scenario is `PARTIAL`, none are `FAIL`
   257	- `FAIL`: any mapped scenario is `FAIL`
   258	
   259	Hard rule:
   260	- Any critical-path scenario `FAIL` forces feature verdict to `FAIL`.
   261	
   262	### Release Readiness Rule
   263	
   264	Release is `READY` only when:
   265	
   266	1. No feature verdict is `FAIL`.
   267	2. All critical scenarios are `PASS`.
   268	3. Coverage is 100% of playbook scenarios defined by the root index and backed by per-feature files (`COVERED_FEATURES == TOTAL_FEATURES`).
   269	4. No unresolved blocking triage item remains.
   270	
   271	### Root-vs-Feature Rule
   272	

