    37	## 3. WHAT IT CHECKS
    38	
    39	- **Common (all scanned files)**: UTF-8 readability and LF line endings (flags CRLF).
    40	- **JavaScript (`.js/.cjs`)**: requires `'use strict';` near file top.
    41	- **JavaScript ESM (`.mjs`)**: strict-mode directive is not enforced.
    42	- **TypeScript (`.ts/.tsx/.mts`)**: requires a `MODULE:` header marker near file top, except test files and pattern assets.
    43	- **Python (`.py`)**: requires `#!/usr/bin/env python3` and module docstring near file top.
    44	- **Shell (`.sh`)**: requires `#!/usr/bin/env bash` and `set -euo pipefail` near file top.
    45	- **JSON (`.json`)**: strict parser validation via Python `json` module, with comment-aware fallback for `tsconfig*.json`.
    46	- **JSONC (`.jsonc`)**: comment stripping followed by strict JSON parse.
    47	
    48	### What it does not check
    49	
    50	The verifier is intentionally lightweight. It does not replace the standards
    51	checklists and does not scan markdown prose. These remain manual review gates:
    52	
    53	- exact visual header shape beyond the marker-level checks above;
    54	- naming conventions;
    55	- comment density and WHY-vs-WHAT comment quality;
    56	- KISS/DRY/SOLID judgment;
    57	- JavaScript `module.exports` versus plugin ESM default-export decisions;
    58	- TypeScript package-boundary decisions such as NodeNext ESM versus root
    59	  CommonJS defaults.
