.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/spec.md:3:description: "Deep-research packet that diagnosed why sk-doc scored 20/100 on the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna skill-benchmark. Falsified the ~34-alias-gap premise (113/113 equality) and isolated the real defect: a three-part path-contract problem. Hands a dependency-ordered fix plan to sibling packet 012-sk-doc-routing-fixes."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/spec.md:64:The Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna skill-benchmark scored sk-doc at 20/100 with roughly 19% exact-resource recall. Misses correlated with wrong path-root answers (`create-*` packet prefixes instead of root-relative `references/...` paths) and with over-bundling, including one scenario that routed 65 resources and wasted every one. Going in, the working theory was that around 34 `mode-registry.json` aliases had no literal `hub-router.json` `vocabularyClass` counterpart, making them invisible to the scorer.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/spec.md:128:| Dependency | Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark artifact (`tier2-sk-doc-luna-opencode.report.json`) | Findings need grounding in a scored run | Located under `system-deep-loop/068-skill-benchmark-codex-executor` and cited throughout. It predates today's configs and carries no config fingerprints, so a fresh live run is required after the fix lands to claim repair |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md:36:Diagnose and fix sk-doc's skill-routing foundation so the AI assistant reliably surfaces the right sk-doc reference/document at the right moment — perfect routing (right skill + right files, on demand). Grounded in the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna skill-benchmark: sk-doc scored 20/100 with ~19% exact-resource recall; misses correlate strongly with wrong path-root (answers beginning with create-* prefixes instead of root-relative references/… paths) and with over-bundling (e.g. one scenario routed 65 resources all wasted). Deliverable: prioritized, implementable optimizations to sk-doc's skill-routing templates, routing logic, and JSON config artifacts (hub-router.json, mode-registry.json, command-metadata.json), each tied to the benchmark failure mode it addresses. This is the FOUNDATION phase — findings must be implementable before the remaining skills are researched.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md:179:  - Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna skill-benchmark results for sk-doc (20/100, ~19% exact-resource recall)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/prompts/iteration-4.md:18:Research Topic: sk-doc routing foundation diagnosis and optimization — grounded in Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark (20/100, ~19% exact recall). Quantified failure distribution (iteration 3): 6 wrong-root rows, 6 missing-leaf rows, 5 over-bundle rows, 2 clean; scorer uses exact path equality on model-stated arrays (Mode-B live); sk-doc lacks a second-layer surface router so deterministic replay stops at packet SKILL.md resources
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/prompts/iteration-5.md:18:Research Topic: sk-doc routing foundation diagnosis and optimization — Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark (20/100). Established: 19 rows classify 6 wrong-root / 6 missing-leaf / 5 over-bundle / 2 clean; create-skill teaching mixes packet-root-relative leaf ids with hub-root-relative packet-qualified load addresses without specifying the handoff (4 rows directly explained); SD-020 gold is stale/virtual, SD-016 has provenance contradiction; sk-doc lacks a second-layer surface router
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/prompts/iteration-1.md:18:Research Topic: sk-doc routing foundation diagnosis and optimization — diagnose and fix sk-doc's skill-routing foundation (hub-router.json/mode-registry.json alias coverage, create-skill routing templates, skill-benchmark scorer behavior) grounded in the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark: sk-doc 20/100, ~19% exact-resource recall, wrong path-root answers (create-* prefixes instead of root-relative references/... paths), over-bundling (one scenario routed 65 resources all wasted)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/prompts/iteration-6.md:18:Research Topic: sk-doc routing foundation diagnosis and optimization — Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark (20/100). Established: 6 wrong-root / 6 missing-leaf / 5 over-bundle / 2 clean; create-skill teaching mixes packet-root-relative leaf ids and hub-root-relative load addresses without handoff spec; routing-registry-drift-guard protects only system-deep-loop advisor projections; no guard checks output namespace semantics, recursive packet-leaf coverage, fixture-to-topology validity, or execution-time provenance; sk-doc lacks second-layer surface router
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/prompts/iteration-2.md:18:Research Topic: sk-doc routing foundation diagnosis and optimization — diagnose and fix sk-doc's skill-routing foundation (hub-router.json/mode-registry.json alias coverage, create-skill routing templates, skill-benchmark scorer behavior) grounded in the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark: sk-doc 20/100, ~19% exact-resource recall, wrong path-root answers (create-* prefixes instead of root-relative references/... paths), over-bundling (one scenario routed 65 resources all wasted)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/prompts/iteration-3.md:18:Research Topic: sk-doc routing foundation diagnosis and optimization — diagnose and fix sk-doc's skill-routing foundation (hub-router.json/mode-registry.json alias coverage, create-skill routing templates, skill-benchmark scorer behavior) grounded in the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark: sk-doc 20/100, ~19% exact-resource recall, wrong path-root answers, over-bundling (SD-015: 65 resources all wasted)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/research.md:3:description: "Synthesized findings from a 10-iteration deep-research loop diagnosing sk-doc's skill-routing foundation against the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark (20/100, ~19% exact-resource recall), with a dependency-ordered, implementable fix plan."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/010-sk-doc-routing-research/research/research.md:29:The research charter asked why sk-doc scored 20/100 with ~19% exact-resource recall on the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna skill-benchmark, whether an alleged ~34-alias coverage gap explained it, whether create-skill's routing templates teach the wrong path-root convention, how the scorer actually reads a hub skill, whether the drift guard catches the gap, and what implementable fixes follow. All five questions were answered with file:line evidence; the fix plan is frozen in Sections 8–10.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/012-sk-doc-routing-fixes/spec.md:44:sk-doc scored 20/100 with roughly 19 percent exact-resource recall on the Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna skill benchmark. The 010 research packet traced the cause to a three-part path-contract defect, not the previously assumed alias coverage gap. This packet turns the research's dependency-ordered nine-step fix plan into an implementation-ready scaffold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/012-sk-doc-routing-fixes/spec.md:74:sk-doc's Tier-2 gpt-5.6-luna benchmark run scored 20/100 with roughly 19 percent exact-resource recall (`tier2-sk-doc-luna-opencode.report.json`). The headline theory blamed a roughly 34-alias coverage gap in the hub router, but the research found 113 of 113 alias-to-vocabularyClass pairs equal with zero gaps. The real defect is a three-part path-contract problem across all 19 benchmark scenarios: 6 rows fail on wrong path-root normalization, 6 rows fail on a missing expected leaf resource and 5 rows lose material recall to an over-bundled resource set. Two rows (SD-008, SD-012) already pass clean and must stay clean through the fix.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/001-3-tier-consistency-standard/spec.md:41:The routing config across the skill fleet is a patchwork. Every unit has an in-document router, but the typed-pair surface (leaf-manifest + resolvable router pairs) exists on only 6 of 12 top-level skills, two playbook shapes coexist (index-table vs frontmatter → two non-comparable gold-provenance methods), and the shared benchmark harness is skill-specific (a hardcoded `MR-`→browser classifier, an sk-code-only path extractor) so it does not score the tiers uniformly. Three independent model reviews (GPT-5.6-SOL, GPT-5.6-LUNA, Fable-5) additionally flagged that the current green `typedPairRecall=1.0` scores may be circular (gold matching the router), so config-coherence is proven but real routing quality is not.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/002-default-mode-policy-research/run2-archive/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md:141:sol-ultra (GPT-5.6-SOL), luna-max (GPT-5.6-LUNA), terra-max (GPT-5.6-TERRA). glm-max is the GLM-5.2 lens.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:106:| REQ-006 | Emit a per-hub `activation-record.json` audit trail (eligibility, CAS transition, rollback proof, real-model verification slot). | Each `activation/<hub>/activation-record.json` records `activated`, `shippedThisRun`, the CAS transition, the rollback proof, and a `realModelVerification` slot. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:112:| REQ-007 | P4a T9 — real-model routing verification per hub on playbook prompts (GPT-5.6-LUNA high/fast, GPT-SOL medium/fast, MiniMax M3). | Complete: recorded in `real-model/<hub>/verdict.json` and each record's `realModelVerification` field; 40/42 pass across 3 models × 7 hubs, **0 wrong-hub routes** (the 2 non-passes are LUNA transport timeouts, correct on run2). Breadth is bounded (2 playbook prompts per hub) and honestly labeled — a sample, not full-corpus. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/lib/activate-hub.cjs:242:    realModelVerification: readExistingRealModel(args.hub),
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/checklist.md:88:  - **Evidence**: Each `activation/<hub>/activation-record.json` records eligibility, the CAS transition, the rollback proof, and a `realModelVerification` slot.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/checklist.md:116:  - **Evidence**: 3 models (LUNA/SOL fast, MiniMax M3) × 7 hubs on authentic playbook prompts; 40/42 pass, **0 wrong-hub routes** (2 non-passes are LUNA transport timeouts, run2 correct). Verdicts in `real-model/<hub>/verdict.json`; each record's `realModelVerification` carries its per-model result.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/tasks.md:72:**Evidence**: Each record reports `rollback.byteExact=true`; the driver never writes under a child path. Real-model verification (T015) is complete and each record's `realModelVerification` carries its per-model verdict.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:47:- `live-gpt-5-6-luna-high/`: model/manual-playbook evidence, advisory to deterministic parity; persist exact `openai/gpt-5.6-luna`, `high`, executor, scenario IDs, and run revision.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:7:The LUNA High invocation is presently environment-scoped, not scenario-scoped: set `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL=openai/gpt-5.6-luna` and `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high`. The executor otherwise defaults to DeepSeek with `high`; it emits `opencode run --model … --variant …`. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:41`, `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:94`, `.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md:139`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:24:  {"id":"F-11-3","area":"benchmark","finding":"LUNA High selection is process-wide environment configuration rather than per-scenario data, while --executor selects only the Codex versus OpenCode transport.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/executor-dispatch.cjs:146","severity":"P1","actionable":"Add an orchestrator-owned scenario execution map with providerModel=openai/gpt-5.6-luna and variant=high, consumed by the new adapter without editing the frozen scenario loader.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-012.md:18:All seven hubs already carry `servingAuthority: compiled, shadowOnly: false` after the P4b flip (verified by reading each `manifest.json` under `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`). Each hub also has a `fence-state.json` (epochs 2–4), a `serving-flip-record.json` (per-flip audit), and an `activation-record.json` (with `realModelVerification.perModelPass` for `luna`/`minimax`/`sol`). These are durable, byte-stable files — but they live only inside the spec tree, and no module path joins them into one machine-readable snapshot.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-012.md:42:`.opencode/specs/.../010-live-activation/real-model/sk-code/verdict.json` records `perModelPass: { luna: "1/2", sol: "2/2", minimax: "2/2" }` and 6 raw prompt transcripts in `raw/luna-1-1.txt` etc. — but it does NOT include the `servingAuthority` or `effectivePolicyHash` at the moment of the LUNA query, so a reader cannot reconstruct "was this hub compiled-serving under the flag when LUNA answered?". F-11-2 already noted the harness scores the model, not the compiled-router; F-12-4 notes the durable archive shape loses the same data the parity gate would need.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:28:`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=<0|1> codex exec --model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="high" -c service_tier="fast" -c approval_policy=never --sandbox read-only -o <stdout-evidence> "<route-only prompt>" 2> <stderr-evidence>`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:30:The model and effort are valid (`cli-codex/SKILL.md:235-242`), and the CLI contract requires explicit model, effort, and service tier (`cli-codex/SKILL.md:267-268`). Keep routing validation read-only and tell LUNA to return the injected advisor skill, compiled action, target mode/packet, and serving status without executing the underlying user task. Treat timeout as `SKIP` with an infrastructure blocker, not routing failure: earlier LUNA routing runs hit the existing 150-second ceiling repeatedly (`010-live-activation/real-model/run-log.txt:50-57`, `:95-102`, `:143-150`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:50:  {"id":"F-3-7","area":"playbooks","finding":"Prior LUNA route runs repeatedly exhausted the 150-second ceiling, so model timeout must be separated from routing correctness.","evidence":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/real-model/run-log.txt:50","severity":"P1","actionable":"Pin gpt-5.6-luna with high effort and explicit fast tier, capture stdout and stderr separately, and record infrastructure timeout as SKIP rather than PASS or routing FAIL.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/live-activation-goal.md:94:  - **GPT-5.6-LUNA** — reasoning `high`, service tier `fast`.
